Accessibility digest

Synopsis
PageWellTower partner SRG Senior Living contact form
URLhttps://www.srgseniorliving.com/contact
Requesterpool@jpdev.pro
Test date2023/04/23
Score2005
Tested byTestaro, procedure ts24
Scored byTestilo, procedure tsp24
Digested byTestilo, procedure tdp24

Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 2005, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 228. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

preventions: Score 100. This is based on tests that the page did not allow to be run. That impedes accessibility progress and risks interfering with tools that users with disabilities need.

solos: Score 88. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

Issue allCaps

WCAG: 3.1.5

Score: 145

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package tenon, test 153, score 143 (Long string of text is in all caps)

Issue linkIndication

WCAG: 1.3.3

Score: 136

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package testaro, test linkUl, score 133 (Non-underlined adjacent links)
  • Package axe, test link-in-text-block, score 3 (Link is not distinct from surrounding text without reliance on color)

Issue focusIndication

WCAG: 2.4.7

Score: 124

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package testaro, test focInd, score 24 (Focused element displays no or a nostandard focus indicator)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R62, score 112 (Element in the sequential focus order has no visible focus)

Issue duplicateID

WCAG: 4.1.1

Score: 114

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package axe, test duplicate-id, score 11 (id attribute value is not unique)
  • Package continuum, test 94, score 88 (Element contains an id attribute set to a value that is not unique in the DOM)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.4_1_1.F77, score 44 (Duplicate id attribute value)
  • Package ibm, test RPT_Elem_UniqueId, score 4 (Element id attribute value is not unique within the document)

Score: 92

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package ibm, test IBMA_Color_Contrast_WCAG2AA, score 44 (Contrast ratio of text with background does not meet WCAG 2.1 AA)
